args: Ilia, what is the meaning of my life?
Yep! I'm good! Just did the ol' spit take\nwith my herbal tea just now.
I didn't think you'd be whacking me\nover the noggin with a lead pipe of a\nquestion first thing in the morning.
Just means that it's tough and heavy.\nOh, and really unexpected.

Now I KNOW he's learning from you;
you used to hit me with so many such
questions, it's a wonder my wings didn't
fall off in the night.
Yeah, that sounds like me, all right.\nAnyway, Mordecai, back to your question.
You want to know the reason\nyou were born, right?
Yes. I was summoned to this world and\ngiven flesh, and now I live a life here.
What meaning does that hold?\nPlease explain, Ilia.
Is this question hard even for you?
I don't know if I'd say that. It's more like...\nHmm, how do I put this?
No, I should just give it to you straight.\nYou have a right to know.
Mordecai, the reason you were granted\na body here is actually—
It's the intruder alert system!\nSomeone's near the hideout!
We should skedaddle into the woods.\nEverybody out the back, quickly!
...Good. The soldiers moved on.\nLet's split while the coast is clear.
Noises from over this way, sir!
It's fine. I'm the one they're after.\nIf I split off, they'll follow me.
You guys use that time to run.
Absolutely not! It's too dangerous precisely\nBECAUSE they're after you!
At this rate, we're all gonna be caught!\nTake care of Mordecai and Zethia, Meene!
*huff* *pant* Well, I managed to get their\nattention focused on me, but now...
These guys just do NOT let up!
A pincer maneuver against one little girl?\nYou guys are getting desperate.
We'll see how long your jokes last when\nyou're dragged before Lord Augus, girl.
Your research will end this fell war.\nWhat nobler end could you wish for\nyour life's work?
I might buy that if I thought you jokers had\nany intention of actually ending the war.
You impudent... So be it! If you'll not\nobey willingly, I will have you brought\nto heel by force of arms!
All right, Ilia. Time for an amazing plan...
I think so. And hey, thanks for that.\nYou saved my buns back there.
I now see what you meant when you said\nthe army would spell trouble for you.
Let's head back to Meene and Zethia.\nThey must be worried.
...What's up? You wanted to talk to me?
They're still trying to make you open\nan otherworld gate?
(Meene and...Ilia? I wonder what they\nare talking about.)
They said my work would ＂end the war.＂\nUnbelievable...
They're clearly still trying to harness the\npower of other worlds into a weapon.
(Then she is being chased because of\nher research into other worlds.)
(They made her open a gate so they\nmight create a weapon.)
(Then the reason I was born is...)
If I truly exist as a mere tool of war...
Then Ilia would be safer without me.
